{
  "stem": "26142.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a train, there was a tunnel through the Carpathian mountain, and that was the only area where a train could go through, because that was done before World War I, yet, that the train-- so they put us on a train, [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] and we arrived on the other side, which was formerly Poland, into a city the next day in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 67
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We arrived into a city called Kolomyja.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Jews would call it Kolomyja.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We stayed in the train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was August already now, probably August the 5th.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a hot, hot day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We stayed a whole day in the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They didn't know what to do, it seems, and [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] I remember it was so hot in the train that we begged the soldiers to let us out of the train.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I got out with my brother, Tsvi, and we found a piece from a fence, a piece of lumber.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We put that down and we laid down on there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that was in Kolomyja.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We stayed there all night and, again, I think we could have run somewhere, but the family ties were so strong that you didn't want to.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You could have, maybe, and you didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Anyway, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the next day, in the morning, we found out that there is a Hungarian Jewish labor unit working the head-- this area was already-- well, when the Germans attacked it, the Hungarians attacked that area, and it was emptied out.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The Russians, they ran.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They practically didn't put up a resistance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was so-- we couldn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We thought that the mighty Soviet Union, if Germany will attack them, then it will break his neck.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
